{"title": "Secret Room", "content": "While searching the Old, Dark House or Haunted Castle for clues, the Amateur Sleuth is likely to come across one of these: a hidden room behind a wall or underneath the floor that can only be revealed by triggering an opening mechanism.\n\nUncovering a Secret Room often marks a turning point in the investigation since these places are always filled with evidence or compromising diaries. Alternatively, these rooms served the owner as a vault and are packed with valuables.\n\nVideo games like to feature these places as Easter Eggs, so expect to solve some puzzles before you can access these rooms. Often, particularly in platformers, a secret room may be concealed by the scenery to the players, but not to the player character.\n\nCompare Secret Path and Secret Underground Passage for convenient ways for characters to sneak in or out of dangerous places.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SecretRoom", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/JourneyIntoMystery", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/KaguyaSamaLoveIsWar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Coraline", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/IndianaJonesAndTheLastCrusade", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Parasite2019", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheBestOffer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/YoungFrankenstein", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/AvengersAgeOfUltron", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheOrphanage", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheGeneralsDaughter", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DonnieDarko", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/DanielPinkwater", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/AgathaChristie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/CSForester", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/RepairmanJack", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HarryPotter", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/HouseOfAnubis", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ArrestedDevelopment", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/GeraldoRivera", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheSuiteLifeOfZackAndCody", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheFlash2014", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoctorWho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php